.TH MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_CPP 3 "July 2026" "mu2edaq-notify 0.1.0" "Mu2e DAQ"
.SH NAME
mu2edaq_notify_cpp \- C++17 publisher library for the Mu2e DAQ
notification server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <mu2edaq_notify/notify.hpp>
// link: -lmu2edaq_notify -lcurl   (CMake: mu2edaq::notify)

mu2edaq::notify::Options opts;   // server_url, fallback_url, token,
                                 // source, host, timeout_ms, discover
mu2edaq::notify::Publisher pub(opts);
bool ok = pub.publish(severity, title, message, meta);
pub.debug(t,m)  pub.info(t,m)  pub.warning(t,m)
pub.error(t,m)  pub.critical(t,m)

mu2edaq::notify::DiscoveredServer d =
    mu2edaq::notify::discover_server_pair(timeout_s);   // d.primary, d.fallback
std::string url = mu2edaq::notify::discover_server(timeout_s);  // primary only
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Publishes events over HTTP using libcurl. Two addresses resolve
independently, each in order Options field > environment > discovery:
\fBserver_url\fR (primary; $MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_URL; the mu2edaq-discovery
ANNOUNCE's own host/port/scheme) and \fBfallback_url\fR (secondary;
$MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_FALLBACK_URL; the same ANNOUNCE's
\fBmeta.fallback_url\fR), used only when Options::discover is true
(UDP multicast 239.255.42.99:28999, filter app=notify). The bearer
token comes from Options::token or $MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_TOKEN.
.PP
publish() tries server_url first and only tries fallback_url when the
primary is unreachable at the transport level (DNS/connection/timeout
failure) -- an explicit rejection from a reachable server (bad token,
bad payload) is not retried against the fallback. Returns true when a
server accepted the event; it never throws on delivery failure. Meta is
a std::map<std::string,std::string>.
.SH BUILDING
.nf
cmake -S . -B build && cmake --build build
ctest --test-dir build     # CppUnit tests when CppUnit is installed
.fi
Works on Linux, macOS, and Windows 11 (MSVC; links ws2_32
automatically).
.SH SEE ALSO
mu2edaq_notify(3), mu2edaq-notify-server(1)
